result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Christopher R. McCorkle was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Christopher R. McCorkle was found guilty of Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant must install Ignition Interlock Device on all vehicles titled in his name upon issuance of avalid drivers license.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
No consumption or possession of alcohol & no entering upon the premises of any business that sells alcohol except to pay for necessities (gas, groceries).
Defendant must submit a DNA sample to the state's data base.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must attend at least one AA meeting per week.

timeConds.notes: Huber and good time allowed. Eligible for community service under 973.09(8).

Called at 1:47 PM. Christipher McCorckle appears in person and with counsel Gary Cirilli. State appears by Jodie Bednar-Clemens. State - resolved - defendant would plead g/nc to counts #1 and #2 as alleged, DRI #3 and dismiss outright count #4, joint recommendation of a withheld sentence and place on probation for 3 years on count #1 and straight sentence on count #2; conditions of probation on count #1 to include: costs,  1 year in FC jail, AODA and follow thru, absolute sobriety, no entry into any bars or taverns and no possession of alcohol, employment/school, 250 hours of community service (free to argue), reimburse $35.00 for blood draw costs; count #2 - $500 fine inclusive of costs - no probation. Cirilli and McCorckle agree and acknowledges 3 prior OWI convictions. McCorckle pleads NC to counts #1 and #2 as alleged. Court DRI #3 and dismisses #4. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutioanl rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sententencing, court insrtructs on minimums for count #1. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - requests 250 hours of community service. Cirilli makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - argues for no community service, 3 days jail credit if revoked (stipulated). State now has no objections to no community service. McCorckle withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #2 - $500 fine inclusive of costs - take bond posted; count #1 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: fine of $600.00 plus costs - take bond posted, 1 year in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.09(8) - report today - credit for 3 days only if revoked, AODA and follow thru, revoke DL for 3 years, IID on DL and all vehicles titled in his name for 3 years commencing upon issuance of valid DL, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, maintain/obtain full time employment/school with verbage, reimburse $35.00 for blood draw costs - take bond posted, submit DNA sample with surcharge assessed - take bond posted, attend at least on AA meeting each week, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on October 1, 2014 at 01:15 pm.

Called at 10:39 AM, also called 14CM137. Christopher McCorkle here and with counsel Gary Cirilli, has information, waives reading, enters NG pleas to all counts, ask for FPT. Court accepts pleas, continues bond on this matter, set for FPT on 10/1/14 at 1:15 PM. On 14CM137 - dismiss #1 of criminal complaint, plead to #2 as alleged - $300 fine plus costs. Cirilli and McCorckle agree. Court dismisses count #1. McCorkle pleads NC to count #2 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to attorney. State - follow joint recommendation. Cirilli - follow joint recommnendation - ask for time to pay at $80.00/month. McCorckle withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #2 - fine of $300 plus costs totalling $931.00 (DNA surcharge and DA surcharge) - paid  at rate of $80.00/month commencing 9/15/14/CO, right to appeal, adjourned.
